# MEMORY.md — Shared Team Memory

> **What this is:** Append-only log of facts, decisions, and handoffs that any agent on the team might need.
>
> **Who writes:** All agents (append only — never delete or rewrite past entries).
>
> **Who reads:** All agents at every wake (last 7 days minimum).
>
> **Format:** One entry per event. Newest entries at the BOTTOM of the file.

---

## Entry format

```
## YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM — [from <agent_name>] <one-line summary>
- <bullet of context, decision, or handoff detail>
- <link or file path if applicable>
- Next: <what should happen next, if anything>
```

---

## Pruning policy

The HUMAN team owner consolidates entries weekly:
- Entries older than 7 days that are still relevant → moved to `KNOWLEDGE.md` (the curated reference)
- Entries older than 7 days that are obsolete → deleted from this file (kept in git history)
- Recent entries (< 7 days) → stay here

Agents NEVER prune. Append-only.

